2025-05-29 22:59:00,126 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 7:
2025-05-29 22:59:00,126 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: How does amortized analysis handle a k-bit counter using the Aggregate Method?
2025-05-29 22:59:00,127 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: In a k-bit counter, the Aggregate Method calculates the total number of bit flips over n increments, which is less than 2n. Since each increment has a worst-case cost of O(k), the total cost is O(n), and the amortized cost per operation is O(1).
