Flashcard 6:
2025-05-29 23:04:38,953 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: How does amortized analysis handle the running time of heap sort?
2025-05-29 23:04:38,953 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Amortized analysis considers the repeated insertions and deletions in heap sort. While each insertion into a heap of size n takes O(log n) time, the total time for n insertions is O(n log n). However, this might be an overestimate since many insertions occur on smaller heaps. Amortized analysis averages the cost over all operations to provide a more accurate total time.
2025-05-29 23:04:38,953 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-29 23:04:38,953 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 7:
2025-05-29 23:04:38,954 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is the amortized cost per operation for a k-bit counter using the Aggregate Method?
2025-05-29 23:04:38,954 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: For a k-bit counter, the total number of bit flips in n increment operations is n + n/2 + n/4 + ... + n/2^k, which is less than 2n. Thus, the total cost is O(n), and the amortized cost per operation is O(n)/n = O(1).
2025-05-29 23:04:38,954 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-29 23:04:38,954 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
