2025-05-29 23:04:38,955 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Aggregate Method first analyzes the entire sequence of operations and then calculates the amortized cost per operation. In contrast, the Accounting Method assigns amortized costs to individual operations upfront and then computes the total cost of the sequence, providing the per-operation cost.
2025-05-29 23:04:38,955 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-29 23:04:38,955 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
